# .worktreeinclude — committed, teammate-shared list of gitignored files that
# Mochi copies into every new session worktree, so an isolated session can run.
#
# Rename this file to `.worktreeinclude` (drop `.example`) and commit it. When
# present it OVERRIDES the per-machine `copyGlobs` project setting. If absent,
# Mochi falls back to that setting, and finally to the default `.env*`.
#
# Format: one glob per line. The last path segment may contain `*`.
# Blank lines and `#` comments are ignored.

.env*
config/*.local.json
certs/*.pem
